      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHAD POWERS (8) tends to drift back and work into the race, charging home into the minors two back before winding up late into second (19.97) in a Grade 5 at this track last time. Has never missed the frame at the trip from four starts. Makes plenty of appeal. TEA ROSE (3) continues to race in super honest form hitting the frame at all eight career runs, winning two back before finishing second last time (20.11) over 366m at this track. Has a good overall strike-rate and can find the frame here. BOMB SUE (7) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when eighth at Q Lakeside over 390m behind Tusken Warrior (22.77) in a Grade 5. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. One of the main contenders. THREE GIRLS (2) in the money here last time and looks a top-three prospect again.",
